The paper deals with video anomaly detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves correcting noisy labels using a graph convolutional network, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves supervised learning and classification tasks, which fall under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments involve datasets with videos, which is a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper deals with anomaly detection, which is a subfield of computer security (cs.CR).
